      "id": 21552,
      "category": "researcher",
      "content": "Here is one of my first  ( valid ) report as hunter.\n\nI found an easy way, requesting minimal victim interaction execpted the simple fact to click on a link, to crash the victim's host quickly. It was possible throught  a slack URL used for accessing to the Staging environment : `slack://open?devEnv=staging` .  When used, there had no check if a Slack instance was already opened and by hence an infinite number of instances could be started.\nThe result was a quick CPU and RAM overhelmed finally resulting to a sustem's crash.\n\nI provided a simple POC page showing the issue with different levels ( 10 instances, 20, 50, 1à00, 1000 ).",
